snippet.textDisplay: It's scary to hear about epidemic  but thinking back on it now sixteen years later, I wasn't scared to be in Toronto during the height of it. I thought we were honestly getting a back rap for nothing, since the number of cases was actually low and it seemed overall, pretty well contained. But also thinking about it now, I think I was skeptical of it all because I knew there were rigorous safety measures that were in place that were well display, like the news interviews and public health notices ( I vaguely remember seeing them all over the place and it's only vague because it was sixteen years ago) so I have to give it to Health Canada, they handled SARS and the Ebola scare of 2013 like a pro.
